{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ζών-η</b>, ἡ, <br /> (ζώννυμι) <b>belt, girdle</b>: <br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> properly <b>the lower girdle worn by women</b> just <b>above the hips</b>, περὶ δὲ ζώνην βάλετ᾽ ἰξυῖ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 5.231, 10.544, compare 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 14.181, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.51, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] —Phrases: <br /><Level3><b>__I.1</b></Level3> λῦσε δὲ παρθενίην ζ. unloosed her maiden <b>girdle</b>, of the bridegroom, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 11.245, compare “Lyric poetry” “Alex.Adesp.” 11.18, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Lycurgus” 15 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>middle</i>, of the bride, μούνῳ ἑνὶ ζώναν ἀνέρι λυσαμένα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Anthologia Graeca” 7.324 (hence ζώνη\">Refs</a>], <i>absolutely</i>, of <b>marriage</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Taurica” 204 (Lyric poetry) \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of <b>sexual intercourse</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Philostratus Sophista “Vita Apollonii” 7.6): but also, \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__I.1.b</b></Level4> ζ. λῦσαι to loose <b>the girdle</b> for childbirth, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Hyperides Orator “Fragmenta” 67 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; later λύσασθαι or ἀπολύσασθαι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Hymnus in Delum” 209, 3rd c.AD: Oppianus Apamensis Epicus “Cynegetica” 3.56; so ζώναν κατατίθεσθαι 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 6.39. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__I.1.c</b></Level4> of men on a march, ζ. λύσασθαι to slacken one's <b>belt</b>, i.e. rest oneself, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.120; ζ. ἀναλύεσθαι 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Hymnus in Delum” 237. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.2</b></Level3> of pregnant women, τέκνων ἤνεγχ᾽ ὑπὸ ζώνην βάρος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 1000 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; πῶς γάρ σ᾽ ἔθρεψεν ἐντὸς.. ζώνη; [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Eu.” 608; τοῦτον.. ἔφερον ζώνης ὕπο 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 762 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also ὑπὸ ζώνῃ θέσθαι to <b>conceive,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" hymnus ad Venerem 255. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.3</b></Level3> proverbial, εἰς ζώνην δεδόσθαι to be given <b>for girdle-money</b> (as we should say, <b>pinmoney</b>), of Oriental queens who had cities given them for their small expenses, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 1.4.9; ἣν [χώραν] καλεῖν.. ζ. τῆς βασιλέως γυναικός 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus Alcaeus1.123b. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> man's <b>belt</b> (more frequently ζωστήρ), ἡ ζ. τοῦ Ὠρίωνος the three stars that form the <b>belt</b> of Orion. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Meteorologica” 343b24 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; the <b>belt</b> of barbarians, in which they wore the dagger, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 1.6.10, 4.7.16, 4th c.BC: Theopompus Historicus 39a, 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Anach.” 33, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Hp.Mi.” 368c. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.b</b></Level4> belt used as a <b>purse,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" PRyl. 127.32(1st c.AD), NT.Matt.10.9, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.665b; ζ. χρυσίον 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Fug.” 31. \">NT+1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>part round which the girdle passed, waist</b>, Ἄρεϊ ζώνην ἴκελος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.479 (misunderstood by 2nd c.AD: Pausanias Periegeta 9.17.3), compare 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 11.234, 5th-6th c.AD: Orphica “Fragmenta” 168.28, 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus cited in 1st c.AD: Erotianus Grammaticus (also explained as ={ὀσφύς}). \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> = Latin <i>cingulum</i>, <b>belt</b> worn by Roman civil and military officers, [[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Demodocus Lyricus] 5 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; ={ἀξίωμα}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 10th c.AD: Suidas Legal icographus \">Refs</a>]; οἱ ὑπὸ ζώνην <b>soldiers</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Anonymus cited in [same work]see {αὐθεντήσαντα},compare “Codex Justinianus [4th-6th c.AD]” 1.5.12.6, 11, 6th c.AD: Justinianus Imperator “Edict.” 13.26, “PLond.” 5.1680.21 (6th c.AD). \">Refs 6th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>anything that goes round like a belt</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.935a, 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Musc.Enc.” 3 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; of the <b>girdle</b> of ocean, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Porphyrius Tyrius Philosophus “adversus Christianos - Abh. Berl. Akad.” 69. \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> <b>one of the zones of the terrestrial sphere,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Stoic. 2.195, 2nd-1st c.BC: Posidonius Historicus cited in 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 2.2.2, “Placita Philosophorum” 2.12.1 (_plural_), etc.\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; ζ. διακεκαυμένη, εὔκρατος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 1.2.24, 1.4.6. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__III.2.b</b></Level4> <b>one of the planetary spheres</b>, οἱ μὲν [τῶν πλανητῶν] ὑψηλὴν ζ. φέρονται οἱ δὲ ταπεινήν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Diogenes Oenoandensis Epicureus 8, compare 2nd c.AD: Vettius Valens Astrologus 26.18, “Corpus Hermeticum” 1.25. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__III.2.c</b></Level4> Astrology texts,= ζῴδιον, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Porphyrius Tyrius Philosophus “in Ptolemaei Tetrabiblon” 186. \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.3</b></Level3> in Architecture texts,= διάζωμα, <b>frieze</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Pausanias Periegeta 5.10.5. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.4</b></Level3> Latin <i>zona</i>, in in Medicine texts, <b>shingles</b>, Scrib.Larg.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 63, 247; compare ζωστήρ 111.3. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.5</b></Level3> <b>stripes</b> on fish, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus “De Natura Animalium - Ar.Byzantine Epit.” 3.28, +others \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> <i>plural</i>, an order of divine beings presiding over, or <b>engirdled with</b> cosmic <b>zones</b>, opposed to ἄζωνοι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.AD: Damascius Philosophus “de Principiis” 96, 5th c.AD: Proclus Philosophus “in Platonis Parmenidem commentarii” p.494S. \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G2223","accentedUnicode":"ζώνη","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G2218","matchingForm":"ζυγός","stepTransliteration":"zugos","gloss":"yoke/scales","_zh_tw_Gloss":"軛","_es_Gloss":"yugo/balanza","_zh_Gloss":"轭"},{"strongNumber":"G2224","matchingForm":"ζώννυμι","stepTransliteration":"zōnnumi","gloss":"to dress","_zh_tw_Gloss":"束上","_es_Gloss":"vestir","_zh_Gloss":"束上"}],"shortDef":"belt, sash","mediumDef":"belt, sash <br /><b>a zone, belt, girdle,sash</b> <ref='Mat.3.4; 10:9'>Mt. 3:4; 10:9</ref>; <ref='Mrk.1.6; 6:8'>Mk. 1:6; 6:8</ref>; <ref='Act.21.11'>Acts 21:11;</ref> <ref='Rev.1.13'>Rev. 1:13;</ref> 15:6*","stepGloss":"belt/sash/girdle","stepTransliteration":"zōnē","count":8,"_es_Definition":"cinturón ; cinturón donde guardar dinero (MAT.10:9: MAR.6:8)","_zh_tw_Definition":"腰帶, 皮帶","_zh_Definition":"腰带, 皮带","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"đai thắt; dây lưng","_zh_tw_Gloss":"帶","_es_Gloss":"cinturón/faja","_zh_Gloss":"带"}]}